==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Colony counter
<hw>Col"o*ny count`er</hw> <pr>(k⟦ocr⟧l"⟦osl⟧*n⟦ycr⟧
kount"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Microbiology)</fld> <def>an
instrument designed to conveniently count or assist counting colonies{9}
of microorganisms on a plate containing a gelled growth medium. One
variety uses a pencil-like rod with a metal tip, which is connected by
an electrical connection to the gelled growth medium; when touched to a
colony{9} on the plate, the completion of the electrical circuit causes
an increment of 1 unit on the readout of the colony counter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Colophany</ent>⟦br⟧
